931 static StringRef sanitizeFunctionName(StringRef funcName) { 0
932 // Filter out empty names and names containing null bytes, those can't be in ----
933 // our table. ----
934 if (funcName.empty() || funcName.contains('\0')) 0
935 return StringRef(); 0
936 ----
937 // Check for \01 prefix that is used to mangle __asm declarations and ----
938 // strip it if present. ----
939 return GlobalValue::dropLLVMManglingEscape(funcName); 0
940 } ----

942 bool TargetLibraryInfoImpl::getLibFunc(StringRef funcName, LibFunc &F) const { 0
943 funcName = sanitizeFunctionName(funcName); 0
944 if (funcName.empty()) 0
945 return false; 0
946 ----
947 const auto *Start = std::begin(StandardNames); 0
948 const auto *End = std::end(StandardNames); 0
949 const auto *I = std::lower_bound(Start, End, funcName); 0
950 if (I != End && *I == funcName) { 0
951 F = (LibFunc)(I - Start); 0
952 return true; 0
953 } ----
954 return false; 0
955 } ----
956 ----
957 // Return true if ArgTy matches Ty. ----
958 ----
959 static bool matchType(FuncArgTypeID ArgTy, const Type *Ty, unsigned IntBits, 0
960 unsigned SizeTBits) { ----
961 switch (ArgTy) { 0
962 case Void: 0
963 return Ty->isVoidTy(); 0
964 case Bool: 0
965 return Ty->isIntegerTy(8); 0
966 case Int16: 0
967 return Ty->isIntegerTy(16); 0
968 case Int32: 0
969 return Ty->isIntegerTy(32); 0
970 case Int: 0
971 return Ty->isIntegerTy(IntBits); 0
972 case IntPlus: 0
973 return Ty->isIntegerTy() && Ty->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() >= IntBits; 0
974 case IntX: 0
975 return Ty->isIntegerTy(); 0
976 case Long: 0
977 // TODO: Figure out and use long size. ----
978 return Ty->isIntegerTy() && Ty->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() >= IntBits; 0
979 case Int64: 0
980 return Ty->isIntegerTy(64); 0
981 case LLong: 0
982 return Ty->isIntegerTy(64); 0
983 case SizeT: 0
984 case SSizeT: ----
985 return Ty->isIntegerTy(SizeTBits); 0
986 case Flt: 0
987 return Ty->isFloatTy(); 0
988 case Dbl: 0
989 return Ty->isDoubleTy(); 0
990 // TODO: Tighten this up. ----
991 case LDbl: 0
992 return Ty->isFloatingPointTy(); 0
993 case Floating: 0
994 return Ty->isFloatingPointTy(); 0
995 case Ptr: 0
996 return Ty->isPointerTy(); 0
997 case Struct: 0
998 return Ty->isStructTy(); 0
999 default: 0
1000 break; 0
1001 } ----
1002 ----
1003 llvm_unreachable("Invalid type"); 0
1004 } ----
1005 ----
1006 bool TargetLibraryInfoImpl::isValidProtoForLibFunc(const FunctionType &FTy, 0
1007 LibFunc F, ----
1008 const Module &M) const { ----
1009 unsigned NumParams = FTy.getNumParams(); 0
1010 ----
1011 switch (F) { 0
1012 // Special handling for functions: ----
1013 case LibFunc_cabs: 0
1014 case LibFunc_cabsf: ----
1015 case LibFunc_cabsl: { ----
1016 Type *RetTy = FTy.getReturnType(); 0
1017 if (!RetTy->isFloatingPointTy()) 0
1018 return false; 0
1019 ----
1020 Type *ParamTy = FTy.getParamType(0); 0
1021 // NOTE: These prototypes are target specific and currently support ----
1022 // "complex" passed as an array or discrete real & imaginary parameters. ----
1023 // Add other calling conventions to enable libcall optimizations. ----
1024 if (NumParams == 1) 0
1025 return (ParamTy->isArrayTy() && ParamTy->getArrayNumElements() == 2 && 0
1026 ParamTy->getArrayElementType() == RetTy); 0
1027 else if (NumParams == 2) 0
1028 return ParamTy == RetTy && FTy.getParamType(1) == RetTy; 0
1029 ----
1030 return false; 0
1031 } ----
1032 // Special handling for the sincospi functions that return either ----
1033 // a struct or vector: ----
1034 case LibFunc_sincospi_stret: 0
1035 case LibFunc_sincospif_stret: { ----
1036 if (NumParams != 1) 0
1037 return false; 0
1038 ----
1039 Type *RetTy = FTy.getReturnType(); 0
1040 Type *ParamTy = FTy.getParamType(0); 0
1041 if (auto *Ty = dyn_cast(RetTy)) { 0
1042 if (Ty->getNumElements() != 2) 0
1043 return false; 0
1044 return (Ty->getElementType(0) == ParamTy && 0
1045 Ty->getElementType(1) == ParamTy); 0
1046 } ----
1047 ----
1048 if (auto *Ty = dyn_cast(RetTy)) { 0
1049 if (Ty->getNumElements() != 2) 0
1050 return false; 0
1051 return Ty->getElementType() == ParamTy; 0
1052 } ----
1053 ----
1054 return false; 0
1055 } ----
1056 ----
1057 default: 0
1058 break; 0
1059 } ----
1060 ----
1061 unsigned IntBits = getIntSize(); 0
1062 unsigned SizeTBits = getSizeTSize(M); 0
1063 unsigned Idx = 0; 0
1064 ----
1065 // Iterate over the type ids in the function prototype, matching each ----
1066 // against the function's type FTy, starting with its return type. ----
1067 // Return true if both match in number and kind, inclduing the ellipsis. ----
1068 Type *Ty = FTy.getReturnType(), *LastTy = Ty; 0
1069 const auto &ProtoTypes = Signatures[F]; 0
1070 for (auto TyID : ProtoTypes) { 0
1071 if (Idx && TyID == Void) 0
1072 // Except in the first position where it designates the function's ----
1073 // return type Void ends the argument list. ----
1074 break; 0
1075 ----
1076 if (TyID == Ellip) { 0
1077 // The ellipsis ends the protoype list but is not a part of FTy's ----
1078 // argument list. Except when it's last it must be followed by ----
1079 // Void. ----
1080 assert(Idx == ProtoTypes.size() - 1 || ProtoTypes[Idx + 1] == Void); 0
1081 return FTy.isFunctionVarArg(); 0
1082 } ----
1083 ----
1084 if (TyID == Same) { 0
1085 assert(Idx != 0 && "Type ID 'Same' must not be first!"); 0
1086 if (Ty != LastTy) 0
1087 return false; 0
1088 } else { ----
1089 if (!Ty || !matchType(TyID, Ty, IntBits, SizeTBits)) 0
1090 return false; 0
1091 LastTy = Ty; 0
1092 } ----
1093 ----
1094 if (Idx == NumParams) { 0
1095 // There's at least one and at most two more type ids than there are ----
1096 // arguments in FTy's argument list. ----
1097 Ty = nullptr; 0
1098 ++Idx; 0
1099 continue; 0
1100 } ----
1101 ----
1102 Ty = FTy.getParamType(Idx++); 0
1103 } ----
1104 ----
1105 // Return success only if all entries on both lists have been processed ----
1106 // and the function is not a variadic one. ----
1107 return Idx == NumParams + 1 && !FTy.isFunctionVarArg(); 0
1108 } ----
1109 ----
1110 bool TargetLibraryInfoImpl::getLibFunc(const Function &FDecl, 0
1111 LibFunc &F) const { ----
1112 // Intrinsics don't overlap w/libcalls; if our module has a large number of ----
1113 // intrinsics, this ends up being an interesting compile time win since we ----
1114 // avoid string normalization and comparison. ----
1115 if (FDecl.isIntrinsic()) return false; 0
1116 ----
1117 const Module *M = FDecl.getParent(); 0
1118 assert(M && "Expecting FDecl to be connected to a Module."); 0
1119 ----
1120 return getLibFunc(FDecl.getName(), F) && 0
1121 isValidProtoForLibFunc(*FDecl.getFunctionType(), F, *M); 0
1122 } ----

1242 bool TargetLibraryInfoImpl::isFunctionVectorizable(StringRef funcName) const { 0
1243 funcName = sanitizeFunctionName(funcName); 0
1244 if (funcName.empty()) 0
1245 return false; 0

1250 } ----
1251 ----
1252 StringRef TargetLibraryInfoImpl::getVectorizedFunction(StringRef F, 0
1253 const ElementCount &VF, ----
1254 bool Masked) const { ----
1255 F = sanitizeFunctionName(F); 0
1256 if (F.empty()) 0
1257 return F; 0
1258 std::vector::const_iterator I = ----
1259 llvm::lower_bound(VectorDescs, F, compareWithScalarFnName); 0
1260 while (I != VectorDescs.end() && StringRef(I->ScalarFnName) == F) { 0
1261 if ((I->VectorizationFactor == VF) && (I->Masked == Masked)) 0
1262 return I->VectorFnName; 0
1263 ++I; 0
1264 } ----
1265 return StringRef(); 0
1266 } ----
